r working with Node 20.\n\nAdd the package to your `\"devDependencies\"`:\n\n```sh\nnpm install --save-dev @tsconfig/node20\nyarn add --dev @tsconfig/node20\n```\n\nAdd to your `tsconfig.json`:\n\n```json\n\"extends\": \"@tsconfig/node20/tsconfig.json\"\n```\n\n---\n\nThe `tsconfig.json`: \n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"https://www.schemastore.org/tsconfig\",\n  \"_version\": \"20.1.0\",\n\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"lib\": [\"es2023\"],\n    \"module\": \"nodenext\",\n    \"target\": \"es2022\",\n\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"node16\"\n  }\n}\n\n```\n\nYou can find the [code here](https://github.com/tsconfig/bases/blob/master/bases/node20.json).\n","repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/tsconfig/bases.git","directory":"bases"},"_source_registry_name":"default"}